Pakistan took the western part of Kashmir and India the eastern. Srinagar has 150 mosques. On Monday, an around-the-clock curfew was lifted from 5 a. At least 72 people have been killed since the crackdown began Jan 20 in an effort to curb attacks on government officials and buildings. The need of the hour is development. We are fighting a handful of terrorists who are determined to create a law and order problem, said Jagmohan, a Hindu with a reputation for toughness. Intelligence reports suggest the government has an advantage because the separatists are not united. 